# AMR-GigaWord 200k

# ::id 0 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok yemeni police arrested a woman on suspicion of mailing a pair of bombs powerful enough to take down airplanes , officials said saturday as details emerged about a terrorist plot aimed at the u.s. that exploited security gaps in the worldwide shipping system .
# ::alignments
(s / say-01
      :ARG0 (o / official)
      :ARG1 (a / arrest-01
            :ARG0 (p / police
                  :mod (c / country
                        :name (n / name
                              :op1 "Yemen")))
            :ARG1 (w / woman)
            :ARG2 (s2 / suspect-01
                  :ARG1 (m / mail-01
                        :ARG0 w
                        :ARG1 (b / bomb
                              :quant 2
                              :ARG1-of (p2 / powerful-02
                                    :ARG2-of (h / have-degree-91
                                          :ARG1 b
                                          :ARG3 (e / enough)
                                          :ARG6 (t / take-down-22
                                                :ARG0 b
                                                :ARG1 (a2 / airplane))))))
                  :ARG2 w))
      :time (d / date-entity
            :weekday (s3 / saturday))
      :time (e2 / emerge-02
            :ARG0 (d2 / detail
                  :topic (p3 / plot-01
                        :ARG0 (t2 / terrorist)
                        :ARG1-of (a3 / aim-02
                              :ARG2 (p4 / person
                                    :mod c
                                    :name n
                                    :op1 "U.S."))))
            :ARG0-of (e3 / exploit-01
                  :ARG1 (g / gap
                        :mod (s4 / security)
                        :location (s5 / system
                              :mod (s6 / ship-01)
                              :location (w2 / worldwide))))))

# ::id 1 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

                              :ARG0 (s4 / state)))))
      :ARG1 (k / keep-04
            :ARG0 (c3 / change-01
                  :ARG1 (p2 / policy-01)
                  :ARG1-of (a / aim-02
                        :ARG2 (ii / improve-01
                              :ARG0 c3
                              :ARG1 (p3 / perform-02
                                    :ARG1 (f / finance)))))
            :ARG1 (p4 / person
                  :mod (p5 / poor)
                  :quant (s5 / some)
                  :ARG0-of (h2 / have-rel-role-91
                        :ARG2 (p6 / patient))
                  :ARG1-of h2)
            :ARG2 (g / get-01
                  :ARG0 p4
                  :ARG1 (c4 / care-03
                        :mod (m / medicine)))))

                  :ord (o / ordinal-entity
                        :value 3))

      :op2 (s / say-01

                  :op1 (ii / invest-01

                                    :mod (n4 / next)))))))
